  "prompt": "What's a good moveset for Rockruff in Pokemon Sun and Moon?",
  "response": "Rockruff is a Rock-type Pok\u00e9mon with some decent moves available to it in Pok\u00e9mon Sun and Moon. Here are some recommendations for a good moveset:\n\n1. **Stone Edge**: A powerful Rock-type move with high critical hit ratio.\n2. **Crunch**: A Dark-type move that can lower the defense of the opponent.\n3. **Fire Fang**: To cover against Grass- and Bug-type Pok\u00e9mon which Rockruff is weak against.\n4. **Thunder Fang**: To deal with Water-type Pok\u00e9mon, which are also a threat to Rockruff.\n\nAlternatively, you may want to consider using moves like:\n\n- **Rock Slide**: For a reliable Rock-type STAB move with a chance to flinch.\n- **Accelerock**: A priority Rock-type move available to Rockruff.\n- **Howl**: To boost Rockruff's Attack stat.\n- **Iron Head**: For coverage against Fairy-type Pok\u00e9mon.\n\nThese moves will give Rockruff a balanced and versatile move pool, allowing it to handle a variety of opponents effectively.",
